      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "> Hmm, but isn't it possible that a potentially corrupted signature ends up in PSBT?\r\n\r\nBut we still use `VerifyScript` at the end of `ProduceSignature`. Even so, if there is memory corruption which results in the signature copied into the PSBT being invalid, verifying immediately after signing wouldn't protect against that.",
